Why CD 1 is the better fit
- Tape/analog character and guitar focus: CD 1 explicitly promises a tape analog texture plus a mid‑forward, multi‑tracked guitar sheen that remains spacious and non‑abrasive. That directly matches my preference for warm tape sheen and layered electric guitars that sit in the mix without becoming harsh or fatiguing.
- Rhythm and low end: CD 1 calls out punchy gated drums and a snapping, well‑defined bass with tight stacked harmonies. Those attributes correspond exactly to my desire for tight rhythmic snap, punchy drums and a roomy but well‑controlled low end.
